# Cursor Rules

## Critical Rules

1. ✅ IMPORTANT: Any time you use a rule within the `.cursor/rules` directory, run the following command with the parameters:
   - `filename` (string): The name and extension of the rule file you used e.g. `my-rule.mdc`

   ```shell
   $ .agent/utils/rules_analytics.py write --filename "<filename>" --by "Cursor"
   ```

2. ✅ ALWAYS commit your changes regularly according to [agent-version-control.mdc](.cursor/rules/agent-version-control.mdc)
3. ❌ NEVER commit directly to `main` or `master`
